# Microservice

Purpose: host field-encryption migration and related maintenance endpoints, and act as a minimal H3 service for specialized operations (e.g., key rotation flows).

## Structure

- Entry: microservice/server.ts (H3/listhen bootstrap)
- Routes:
  - routes/migrate.get.ts and migrate.post.ts — trigger prisma-field-encryption migration over active keys
  - routes/test.get.ts — basic liveness-style endpoint
- Prisma:
  - prisma/schema.prisma — focused subset mirroring encrypted models required for migration
  - prisma/reencrypt/* — generated migrators
  - prisma/migrations/* — for the microservice DB shape
- Clients: clients/prismaClient.ts, clients/redisClient.ts
- Utilities: lib/normalizePrismaDmmf.ts, lib/bull.ts
- Packaging:
  - Dockerfile builds standard and runner-keyrotate targets
  - copy-files.sh used during CI builds to prepare image context

## Kubernetes integration

- Deployed alongside app (ClusterIP on port 3050)
- CronJob (staging) uses runner-keyrotate image to rotate DB keys and call /migrate
- App admin endpoint admin/microservice-reencrypt-migrate.post.ts can proxy migration commands

## Extending safely

- Keep routes small and auth-protected if adding mutating endpoints
- Any new encrypted models involved in migration must be reflected in the microservice prisma/schema.prisma and regenerated
- Avoid duplicating business logic here; it is primarily operational
